> Seasoned roasted cauliflower replaces the fried fish in these Baja-style tacos for a perfect vegan dinner idea!

Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 450 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Cut @cauliflower florets{10%ounce} into bite-size pieces if necessary.

Toss cauliflower on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of @cooking oil{2%teaspoon}, half the @blackening spice{1%tablespoon}, @salt{} and @pepper{}. Roast on top rack until cauliflower is slightly charred and tender, ~{20-25%minutes}.

Meanwhile, halve @jalapeño{1} lengthwise, removing ribs and seeds for less heat; thinly slice into half-moons. Thinly slice @radishes{3}. Zest and halve @lime{1}. Roughly chop @cilantro{¼%ounce}.

In a #small microwave-safe bowl{}, combine jalapeño, radishes, juice from half the lime, @sugar{1%tsp}, and a pinch of salt. Microwave for ~{30%seconds}; set aside to pickle, stirring occasionally.

In a #medium bowl{}, combine @red cabbage and carrot mix{4%ounce}, half the cilantro, half the lime zest, juice from remaining lime, @sugar{1%tsp}, and salt and pepper to taste.

In a second #small bowl{}, combine @vegan chipotle mayonnaise{4%tablespoon}, @water{1%tsp}, and a pinch of lime zest to taste. Season with salt and pepper.

Once cauliflower is done roasting, wrap @flour tortillas{6} in damp #paper towels{} and microwave until warm and pliable, ~{30%seconds}.

Divide tortillas between plates. Spread half the chipotle-lime mayo in a line across the center of tortillas; fill with cabbage slaw (draining first) and cauliflower.

Top tacos with @guacamole{4%tablespoon}, remaining chipotle-lime mayo, and as many pickled veggies (draining first) as you like. Garnish with remaining cilantro and serve.